      • execute

        public java.util.HashMap<java.lang.String,java.lang.Object> execute()
        Main loop for NSGA2
        The algorithm consists of these steps:
        1. Initiation of population
        2. Crossover, mutation
        3. Construct non dominated sets
        4. Calculate crowded distances
        5. Reconstruct the population£¬ if iteration not end, go to 2

      • getMeanDistance

        public double getMeanDistance(java.util.Set<ParetoSolution> frontExact)
        Description copied from interface: IEvaluate
        To calculate the mean distance between two pareto fronts.
        In order to get the mean distance:
        1. For each point on the heuristic front, we try to find the nearest point from the exact front.
        2. Calculate the distance of these two points and add to the total distance
        3. Calculate the mean of the distance.
        Specified by:
        getMeanDistance in interface IEvaluate
        Parameters:
        frontExact - exact front got by an exact algorithm
        Returns:
        the mean distance between two fronts

      • initGroup

        public java.util.ArrayList<Individual> initGroup(java.util.ArrayList<Job> jobs,
                                                 int nbJobs,
                                                 int nbJobsA)
        Method to initialize the population
        Here we use random strategy to initialize the genes of an individual:
        • for jobs of agent A, choose randomly one job as scheduled.
        • for jobs of agent B, choose randomly one job as scheduled.
        • to verify if this sequence of gene already exists
        • if this gene already exists, re-do the random process. if not, add the individual into the population
        We loop the process above until the population is filled
        Parameters:
        jobs - jobs to schedule
        nbJobs - number of all jobs
        nbJobsA - number of jobs of agent A
        Returns:
        population initialized

      • selection

        public int selection(java.util.ArrayList<Individual> pop)
        selection operation to select one individual to attend the crossover
        1. Select two individual p and q randomly in the current population
        2. If p dominates q, return p. Else return q.
        Parameters:

        Returns:
